<div id="review_3269245768" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3269245768" />
    <a title="Descending Angel" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/54467254-descending-angel"><img alt="Descending Angel" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1507399547p2/54467254.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3269245768?book_show_action=true">Apr 18, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Descending Angel" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Descending Angel" href="/user/show/54467254-descending-angel">Descending Angel</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/54467254-descending-angel?shelf=roth">roth</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3269245768" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer446534995775230475">This book is really great. It&apos;s a unique experience reading it just because of the way it&apos;s structured, diving into metafiction head first, let alone the pull no punches prose of Roth that&apos;s not afraid to push the envelope and be funny at the same time. It&apos;s an intelligent and insightful look at identity, relationships and the role of a writer. A great novel.</span>
  <span id="freeText446534995775230475" style="display:none">This book is really great. It's a unique experience reading it just because of the way it's structured, diving into metafiction head first, let alone the pull no punches prose of Roth that's not afraid to push the envelope and be funny at the same time. It's an intelligent and insightful look at identity, relationships and the role of a writer. A great novel.</span>
  <a data-text-id="446534995775230475" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


