<div id="review_2382777945" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2382777945" />
    <a title="D" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/4277032-d"><img alt="D" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1466334351p2/4277032.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2382777945?book_show_action=true">May 07, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="D" class="user" itemprop="url" name="D" href="/user/show/4277032-d">D</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4277032-d?shelf=english">english</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2382777945" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16241904993596021904">Hard to put down, which is usually not the case when I read a book by Philip Roth. The story is amazing, containing meta-stories, even meta-meta-stories describing a multiverse. Which one is the actual one is not clear, knowing that there are later books containing the Zuckerman character. Due to the rich story/stories, the amount of introspection is kept at just the right amount.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


